Acting director of cricket Corrie van Zyl has been suspended along with Chief Operating Officer Naasei Appiah and commercial manager Clive Eksteen. JOHANNESBURG - Cricket South Africa has suspended interim director Corrie van Zyl just ten days before the start of the second season of the Mzansi Super League. Van Zyl has been suspended along with Chief Operating Officer Naasei Appiah and commercial manager Clive Eksteen. No reason for the suspensions has been provided. READ: Gibson and team sacked in cricket shake up The news comes with the second edition of the Mzansi Super League set to start next week and the Proteas floundering without a permanent coaching structure. CSA is expected to make an official statement on the suspensions on Wednesday.